<center><h1>Guest Chef</h1></center>

<div class="container" id=“guest_chef_intro”>
<p id="guest_chef_intro_text">
As one of London’s premier culinary establishments, Le Brume Salée employs an innovative rotating cast
of acclaimed guest chefs from around the world. These chefs bring their own expertise and culinary experience
to our kitchen, where they create their own specialty menus. This concept allows patrons to both experience
Le Brume Salée’s traditional French cuisine, while also being exposed to diverse international fare.
</p>
</div>
<br>
<br>
<div class="card" id="chef_card_left">
  <img src="noba.jpg" alt="noba" style="width:100%">
  <div class="container">
    <br><center><h4><b>Noba Matsihusa - Japanese/Peruvian fusion</b></h4><center>
    <p class="card_text">Spending his life dedicated to the art to Japanese-Peruvian fusion, in this capacity he has set up numerous restaurants around the world. As a guest chef at Le Brume Salée, he will implement a variety of Japanese-Peruvian fusion. His specialities will seek to expose patrons to the unique flavors found on both sides of the Pacific.
    </p>
  </div>
</div>

<div class="card" id="chef_card_right">
  <img src="erique.jpg" alt="erique" style="width:100%">
  <div class="container">
    <br><center><h4><b>Enrique Olvera - Mexican</b></h4><center>
    <p class="card_text">As arguably the most recognized and heralded current Mexican chef, Enrique Olvera will take on the duties as guest chef at Le Brume Salée,  where he plans on bringing concepts from his current restaurants. Specifically, he seeks to incorporate his love for locally sourced ingredients into his new kitchen.
    </p>
  </div>
</div>

